 {"id":"bd-10i.4.2","title":"Implement LinkRegistry for OSC 8 hyperlinks","description":"# Implement LinkRegistry for OSC 8 hyperlinks

## Objective
Implement URL storage and ID management for OSC 8 hyperlinks.

## Background: OSC 8 Hyperlinks
Modern terminals support clickable hyperlinks via OSC 8:
- Start link: ESC ] 8 ; ; URL ESC \\
- End link: ESC ] 8 ; ; ESC \\

Multiple cells can share the same link by using the same link ID. The registry deduplicates URLs and manages IDs.

## Technical Design

### Structure
pub struct LinkRegistry {
    links: Vec<Option<String>>,      // ID -> URL mapping
    lookup: HashMap<String, u32>,    // URL -> ID for dedup
    free_list: Vec<u32>,            // Reusable IDs
}

### Implementation
impl LinkRegistry {
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        Self {
            links: Vec::new(),
            lookup: HashMap::new(),
            free_list: Vec::new(),
        }
    }

    /// Register a URL, returning existing ID if present
    pub fn register(&mut self, url: &str) -> u32 {
        // Check for existing
        if let Some(&id) = self.lookup.get(url) {
            return id;
        }

        // Allocate new ID
        let id = self.free_list.pop().unwrap_or_else(|| {
            let idx = self.links.len() as u32;
            self.links.push(None);
            idx
        });

        self.links[id as usize] = Some(url.to_string());
        self.lookup.insert(url.to_string(), id);
        id
    }

    /// Get URL for ID
    pub fn get(&self, id: u32) -> Option<&str> {
        self.links.get(id as usize)
            .and_then(|slot| slot.as_ref())
            .map(|s| s.as_str())
    }

    /// Unregister a link (for cleanup)
    pub fn unregister(&mut self, id: u32) {
        if let Some(Some(url)) = self.links.get(id as usize).cloned() {
            self.lookup.remove(&url);
            self.links[id as usize] = None;
            self.free_list.push(id);
        }
    }

    /// Check if ID is valid
    pub fn contains(&self, id: u32) -> bool {
        self.links.get(id as usize)
            .map(|slot| slot.is_some())
            .unwrap_or(false)
    }

    pub fn len(&self) -> usize {
        self.links.iter().filter(|l| l.is_some()).count()
    }
}

## Link Lifecycle in Rendering
1. When drawing a cell with a link:
   - Register URL with registry
   - Store link_id in CellAttrs

2. When presenting:
   - Check if link_id changed from tracked state
   - If changed, emit OSC 8 open/close sequences

3. After frame:
   - Links not used can be unregistered (optional GC)

## Tests Required
- [ ] register() returns same ID for same URL
- [ ] register() returns different IDs for different URLs
- [ ] get() retrieves correct URL
- [ ] unregister() frees slot
- [ ] Free list reuses IDs
- [ ] contains() correct for valid/invalid IDs

